From Frank Ball Subject Re Type spesifications CB VFR GT VIDAR OLAF SOLBERG wrote Can somebody tell me what all the letter spesifications on motorcycle models really Example What means the C the B and the R in Honda Or the V S G L and P in Suzuki Honda a V designates a V engine street VF for V VT for V CB is a street bike with an parallel twin or inline cylinder R used to mean race bike but is now also used to mean sport CL was for the old steet scramblers street bikes with high pipes CM was a custom street bike CR is dirt only two strokes XL is dual purpose bike XR was dirt only four stroke but now can be a dual purpose bike if it has an L as a GL is a touring bike Frank Ball M work Hewlett Packard fax home Valley House Drive Seca ' F Rohnert Park CA LAW AMA Dod I'm the